<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<meta charset="ISO-8859-1">
<title>Voter FAQ's</title>

<style>
body {
	font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
	margin: 0;
	padding: 0;
	background-color: #f8f8f8;
}

.faq-container {
	width: 80%;
	margin: 20px auto;
	padding: 20px;
	background-color: #fff;
	box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
}

h1 {
	text-align: center;
}

h2 {
	margin-top: 20px;
}

.faq {
	margin-bottom: 30px;
}

.faq p {
	margin: 10px 0;
}
</style>
</head>
<body>

	<div class="faq-container">
		<h1>Voter FAQ</h1>

		<div class="faq">
			<h2>1. What are the eligibility criteria for voter registration?</h2>
			<p>To register as a voter, individuals must be at least 18 years
				old.</p>
		</div>

		<div class="faq">
			<h2>2. What information is required for voter registration?</h2>
			<p>Voters need to provide personal details and upload a valid ID
				proof during the registration process.</p>
		</div>

		<div class="faq">
			<h2>3. Can a voter login immediately after registration?</h2>
			<p>No, voter login requires approval from the admin. Voters
				cannot access their accounts until admin approval.</p>
		</div>

		<div class="faq">
			<h2>4. What can a voter do upon logging in?</h2>
			<p>Upon login,voters can view the profile and list of all elections. 
				Voters can view the list of candidates
				participating in the election.</p>
		</div>

		<div class="faq">
			<h2>5. How does a voter participate in a poll?</h2>
			<p>Voters can participate in a poll based on their constituency.
				They will have access to cast their vote in the relevant elections.</p>
		</div>

		<div class="faq">
			<h2>6. Is there any action after successfully casting a vote?</h2>
			<p>Yes, after successfully casting a vote, voters can download a
				PDF receipt as confirmation of their participation in the election.</p>
		</div>

	</div>

</body>
</html>